{"type":"message","id":"3acf57e5","parentId":"fd701a05","timestamp":"2026-04-06T13:35:15.043Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"让我快速检查每个技能的 SKILL.md 文件。\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d2c946df6a334f4dae04fde1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"for dir in ~/.openclaw/skills/*/ ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/*/; do\n  name=$(basename \"$dir\")\n  skillmd=\"$dir/SKILL.md\"\n  if [ -f \"$skillmd\" ]; then\n    desc=$(head -3 \"$skillmd\" | grep -i description | head -1)\n    echo \"### $name\"\n    echo \"$desc\"\n    echo \"\"\n  fi\ndone","timeout":15}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":57844,"output":135,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57979,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775482513399,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1f4d8a7f-ae90-4065-88bf-e3e33488490a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"499f37d7","parentId":"3acf57e5","timestamp":"2026-04-06T13:35:15.160Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_d2c946df6a334f4dae04fde1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### claude-code-codingplan\ndescription: Configure Claude Code CLI to use CodingPlan API (compatible OpenAI format). Use when user wants to run Claude Code CLI directly with their CodingPlan API key, or when Claude Code CLI fails with authentication errors.\n\n### self-improving-agent\ndescription: \"Captures learnings, errors, and corrections to enable continuous improvement. Use when: (1) A command or operation fails unexpectedly, (2) User corrects Claude ('No, that's wrong...', 'Actually...'), (3) User requests a capability that doesn't exist, (4) An external API or tool fails, (5) Claude realizes its knowledge is outdated or incorrect, (6) A better approach is discovered for a recurring task. Also review learnings before major tasks.\"\n\n### task_orchestrator\n\n\n### agent-team-orchestration\ndescription: \"Orchestrate multi-agent teams with defined roles, task lifecycles, handoff protocols, and review workflows. Use when: (1) Setting up a team of 2+ agents with different specializations, (2) Defining task routing and lifecycle (inbox → spec → build → review → done), (3) Creating handoff protocols between agents, (4) Establishing review and quality gates, (5) Managing async communication and artifact sharing between agents.\"\n\n### automation-workflows\ndescription: Design and implement automation workflows to save time and scale operations as a solopreneur. Use when identifying repetitive tasks to automate, building workflows across tools, setting up triggers and actions, or optimizing existing automations. Covers automation opportunity identification, workflow design, tool selection (Zapier, Make, n8n), testing, and maintenance. Trigger on \"automate\", \"automation\", \"workflow automation\", \"save time\", \"reduce manual work\", \"automate my business\", \"no-code automation\".\n\n### clawdbot-filesystem\ndescription: Advanced filesystem operations - listing, searching, batch processing, and directory analysis for Clawdbot\n\n### elite-longterm-memory\n\n\n### github-manager\n\n\n### memory-keeper\n\n\n### ontology\ndescription: Typed knowledge graph for structured agent memory. Always active when user mentions: tasks, todo, pending, unresolved, problem, issue, need to do, should do, remember, recall, memory, 记得, 记住, 待办, 问题, 没解决, 有什么, 查询, 搜索 - handles entity creation, querying, linking, and cross-skill data access.\n\n### openclaw-github-assistant\ndescription: Query and manage GitHub repositories - list repos, check CI status, create issues, search repos, and view recent activity.\n\n### proactivity\n\n\n### productivity-automation-kit\n\n\n### self-improving\n\n\n### skill-vetter\ndescription: Security-first vetting protocol for AI agent skills. Never install a skill without vetting it first.\n\n### superpowers\ndescription: Spec-first, TDD, subagent-driven software development workflow.\n\n### task_orchestrator\n\n\n### vercel-deploy\ndescription: Deploy and manage Vercel projects. Use when deploying applications to Vercel, managing environment variables, checking deployment status, viewing logs."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":91,"aggregated":"### claude-code-codingplan\ndescription: Configure Claude Code CLI to use CodingPlan API (compatible OpenAI format). Use when user wants to run Claude Code CLI directly with their CodingPlan API key, or when Claude Code CLI fails with authentication errors.\n\n### self-improving-agent\ndescription: \"Captures learnings, errors, and corrections to enable continuous improvement. Use when: (1) A command or operation fails unexpectedly, (2) User corrects Claude ('No, that's wrong...', 'Actually...'), (3) User requests a capability that doesn't exist, (4) An external API or tool fails, (5) Claude realizes its knowledge is outdated or incorrect, (6) A better approach is discovered for a recurring task. Also review learnings before major tasks.\"\n\n### task_orchestrator\n\n\n### agent-team-orchestration\ndescription: \"Orchestrate multi-agent teams with defined roles, task lifecycles, handoff protocols, and review workflows. Use when: (1) Setting up a team of 2+ agents with different specializations, (2) Defining task routing and lifecycle (inbox → spec → build → review → done), (3) Creating handoff protocols between agents, (4) Establishing review and quality gates, (5) Managing async communication and artifact sharing between agents.\"\n\n### automation-workflows\ndescription: Design and implement automation workflows to save time and scale operations as a solopreneur. Use when identifying repetitive tasks to automate, building workflows across tools, setting up triggers and actions, or optimizing existing automations. Covers automation opportunity identification, workflow design, tool selection (Zapier, Make, n8n), testing, and maintenance. Trigger on \"automate\", \"automation\", \"workflow automation\", \"save time\", \"reduce manual work\", \"automate my business\", \"no-code automation\".\n\n### clawdbot-filesystem\ndescription: Advanced filesystem operations - listing, searching, batch processing, and directory analysis for Clawdbot\n\n### elite-longterm-memory\n\n\n### github-manager\n\n\n### memory-keeper\n\n\n### ontology\ndescription: Typed knowledge graph for structured agent memory. Always active when user mentions: tasks, todo, pending, unresolved, problem, issue, need to do, should do, remember, recall, memory, 记得, 记住, 待办, 问题, 没解决, 有什么, 查询, 搜索 - handles entity creation, querying, linking, and cross-skill data access.\n\n### openclaw-github-assistant\ndescription: Query and manage GitHub repositories - list repos, check CI status, create issues, search repos, and view recent activity.\n\n### proactivity\n\n\n### productivity-automation-kit\n\n\n### self-improving\n\n\n### skill-vetter\ndescription: Security-first vetting protocol for AI agent skills. Never install a skill without vetting it first.\n\n### superpowers\ndescription: Spec-first, TDD, subagent-driven software development workflow.\n\n### task_orchestrator\n\n\n### vercel-deploy\ndescription: Deploy and manage Vercel projects. Use when deploying applications to Vercel, managing environment variables, checking deployment status, viewing logs.","cwd":"/home/ai/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775482515152}}
